```javascript
function slugify(title) {
  return String(title)
    .toLowerCase()
    .replace(/[^a-z0-9]+/g, "-")
    .replace(/^-+|-+$/g, "");
}
```

How it works:
- `toLowerCase()` normalizes case.
- `[^a-z0-9]+` collapses any run of non-alphanumeric chars (punctuation, spaces) into a single hyphen.
- `^-+|-+$` trims leading/trailing hyphens.

